About Keybindings

Keybindings allow the user to quickly perform actions without needing to choose them from the menus.

Menu Keybindings

File menu:
     Ctrl+N - New
     Ctrl+O - Open
     Ctrl+[Space] - Quick Open
     F5 - Reload
     Ctrl+Alt+[Space] - Favorites
     Ctrl+S - Save
     Shift+Ctrl+S - Save As
     Alt+Ctrl+S - Save Copy
     F4 - Browse
     F10 - Rename
     F11 - Delete
     Ctrl+P - Print
     Ctrl+Q - Exit

Edit menu:
     Ctrl+Z - Undo
     Shift+Ctrl+Z, Ctrl+Y - Redo
     Ctrl+X - Cut
     Ctrl+C - Copy
     Ctrl+V - Paste
     Shift+Ctrl+V - Paste Overwrite
     Alt+Ctrl+V - Paste Indent
     Ctrl+A - Select All
     Shift+Ctrl+A - Deselect All

Documents menu:
     Shift+Ctrl+N - New Document
     Shift+Ctrl+O - Open Document
     Shift+Ctrl+Q - Close Document
     Alt+LeftArrow, Shift+Ctrl+Tab - Previous
     Alt+RightArrow, Ctrl+Tab - Next
     Ctrl+M - View All

Search menu:
     Ctrl+F - Find
     Shift+Ctrl+F - Find Selected
     Ctrl+H - Replace
     Shift+Ctrl+H - Replace Selected
     Ctrl+W - Find History
     Shift+Ctrl+W - Replace History
     Ctrl+G, Ctrl+L - Goto
     F6 - Jump to Top
     F7 - Jump to Bottom
     F8 - Jump to Insert

Tools menu:
     Ctrl+B - Add Bookmark
     Shift+Ctrl+B - View Bookmarks
     Ctrl+R - Run Macro
     Shift+Ctrl+R - Run Command
     Shift+Ctrl+T - Insert Time
     Shift+Ctrl+D - Insert Date
     Ctrl+I - Indent
     Shift+Ctrl+I - Unindent
     Ctrl+J - Notes
     Shift+Ctrl+J - Tasks
     Ctrl+E - Collaborative Editing
     Ctrl+U - Upload to Pastebin
     Shift+Ctrl+U - Download from Pastebin
     F2 - Statistics

Options menu:
     F3 - Options
     Ctrl+UpArrow - Enlarge Font
     Ctrl+DownArrow - Shrink Font

Help menu:
     Ctrl+F1 - About
     F1 - Help

Other Keybindings

There are other keybindings not listed in the menus:

* RightClick - Show context menu
* Ctrl+MouseWheelUp - Enlarge font
* Ctrl+MouseWheelDown - Shrink font
* Alt+MouseWheelUp - Scroll up ten lines
* Alt+MouseWheelDown - Scroll down ten lines
* Alt+UpArrow - Scroll up ten lines
* Alt+DownArrow - Scroll down ten lines
* Alt+Return - Toggle between text box and command bar
* MiddleClick - Paste
* MiddleClick on toolbar buttons - Shows help about the button
* Home - "Smart" home key, if enabled
* Escape - Close most dialogs

File Browser Keybindings

File menu:
     Ctrl+N - Create Directory
     Shift+Ctrl+N - Create New File
     F2 - Rename
     F3, Delete - Delete
     Alt+Return - Info
     Ctrl+O - Goto
     F5 - Refresh
     Ctrl+Q - Exit

Folders menu:
     Ctrl+E - Edit Folders

Other keybindings:

* RightClick - Show context menu
* Alt+Left, Backspace - Move back
* Alt+Up - Move up
* DoubleClick - Open file or directory
* Return (in files list) - Open file or directory
* Return (in address bar) - Go to directory

Options Dialog Keybindings

* Ctrl+S - Save the options and close the window
* Shift+Ctrl+S - Save the options without closing the window
* Ctrl+1 - Switch to the Font tab
* Ctrl+2 - Switch to the Interface tab
* Ctrl+3 - Switch to the Editing tab
* Ctrl+4 - Switch to the Searching tab
* Ctrl+5 - Switch to the Network tab
* Ctrl+6 - Switch to the File Browser tab
* Ctrl+7 - Switch to the Menus tab
* Ctrl+8 - Switch to the Macros tab
* Ctrl+9 - Switch to the Code tab
* Ctrl+0 - Switch to the Misc tab

Macro Keybindings

Macros can also be bound to Ctrl+1 through Ctrl+0 by going to "Tools -> Macros -> Change Bindings..." and entering the name of the macro next to the keybinding.